Another way to do CSS (Cascadibg Stlye Sheets: determine colors
Locations extra effects on the tags on your web page)<br>

Here is  typicalin document style
<pre>
b {
  color: #00ff00;
  }
  </pre>br>
  
  I do CSS inside the tag. It overpowers all other methoods<br>
  
  <b > This is bold</b><br>
  <b id="myB1" style="color:#00ff00; background-Color:Blie; "this is bold</br>
  <input type=button value=Change onclick="{
      document.getElementById('myB1').style.color = 'red'
      document.getElementById('myB1').style.backgroundColor = 'yelow'
  }"><br>
  
  
  
 
 <textarea style="position:relative; left:0; top:0; width:200; height:50; ">
 Advanced see if you move this textarea
